Dear Scoping Guide Team, Jia, Yaqi and Zeynep. Good evening!
I'm pleased to announce that Yaqi Zhao has been appointed to lead the Scopi=
ng Guide team. Please join me in congratulating her=97we wish Yaqi and the =
team every success in this important phase of the project.
I=92ve reviewed all the feedback on the draft of the Practical Guide to Pro=
ducing Scoping Reviews of Academic and Grey Literature with AI Tools. To re=
flect the comments received, I=92ve made significant editorial changes to t=
he previous version. The revised document is attached and should now serve =
as the foundation for developing Version 1.0 of the Guide.
The feedback I did not incorporate into the attached version has been group=
ed into three categories:

  1.
Immediate fixes (must be completed)
  2.
New sections to add to the Guide (complete as much as possible by April 28)
  3.
Separate documents to develop (to be considered after the April 28 deadline=
)

Your top priority is to complete the tasks in Groups I and II. Group III ta=
sks should not be started before April 28.
Please begin work immediately on producing Version 1.0 for the April 28 del=
iverable. Everything submitted must meet a high standard of quality. Be sur=
e to collaborate with other teams, especially on areas such as the integrat=
ion of academic and grey literature, human oversight, and deep research.
If you have any questions, need clarification, or would like to brainstorm =
ideas, feel free to reach out.
All the best,
Tony B


________________________________
I. REQUIRE IMMEDIATE FIXES (MUST DO)

  *
Add a Table of Contents
Refer to Comment 1 inserted on page 2 of the Guide.
  *
Add Illustrative Examples for Visual Tools
Include examples that show how to create effective visualizations using AI =
tools.
Refer to Comment 2 in Section 2.4.4 Visualize Insights.
  *
Add Feedback Form Link
Insert a link to the user feedback form.
See Comment 3 at the end of Section 3.4.
  *
Format and Proofread the Guide
Fix spacing, bullet formatting, and any remaining grammatical or formatting=
 errors.
This task requires someone with strong MS Word (.docx) formatting skills!

________________________________
